olor, and planters, as well as writings by the philosophes, royal decrees, and court cases—the author untangles the complex forces of the slave regime that have shaped collective memory. The current nationalization of the memory of slavery in France has turned these once peripheral claims into passionate political and cultural debates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aBlack peoplexCultural assimilationxWest Indies, French. 0aBlacksxCultural assimilationxWest Indies, French. 0aBlacksxCultural assimilationzWest Indies, French. 0aIdentity (Psychology)xWest Indies, French. 0aIdentity (Psychology)zWest Indies, French. 0aMaroonsxWest Indies, French. 0aMaroonszWest Indies, French. 0aMemoryxSocial aspectsxWest Indies, French. 0aMemoryxSocial aspectszWest Indies, French. 0aMythxSocial aspectsxWest Indies, French. 0aMythxSocial aspectszWest Indies, French. 0aPhilosophy, Frenchx18th century. 0aPhilosophy, Frenchy18th century. 0aSlaveryxHistoriographyxWest Indies, French. 0aSlaveryzWest Indies, FrenchxHistoriography. 0aSlavesxEmancipationxWest Indies, French. 0aSlavesxEmancipationzWest Indies, French. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Colonialism & Post-Colonialism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782382065?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782382065423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782382065/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK